routeFacts.name: Niddertalbahn: Bad Vilbel - Stockheim
routeFacts.description: Explore TrainSim Germany's debut route in the Train Sim World series featuring the first German non-electrified passenger line. Set in the 1990s, Niddertalbahn features the DB BR 628 in its classic teal livery. Freight services featuring the DB BR 365 are also included.
routeInfo: Niddertalbahn, also known as the Bahnstrecke Bad Vilbel-Glauburg-Stockheim, is a mostly single-track regional rail line that connects the towns of Bad Vilbel and Glauburg-Stockheim, also passing through Nidderau and Altenstadt. While the Niddertalbahn is a humble route, it intersects with several other mainline routes in the area making it a critical connection to the greater regional rail network.
